{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/69093", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/69093/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/69093/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/69093/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/69093", "id": 563976177, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1NjM5NzYxNzc=", "number": 69093, "title": "Compiler Optimization: Bitfields", "user": {"login": "deeprobin", "id": 10373452, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwMzczNDUy", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10373452?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/deeprobin", "html_url": "https://github.com/deeprobin", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/deeprobin/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/deeprobin/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/deeprobin/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/deeprobin/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/deeprobin/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/deeprobin/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/deeprobin/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/deeprobin/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/deeprobin/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2020-02-12T12:44:50Z", "updated_at": "2020-02-12T12:49:51Z", "closed_at": "2020-02-12T12:49:51Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "# Combine multiple bools to one byte\r\n\r\nA [bool](https://doc.rust-lang.org/reference/types/boolean.html) uses one byte of memory.  Why not combine several booleans?  Assuming false is 0 and true 1, you could use the other bits anyway. This is called a [bitfield](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bit_field). \r\n\r\n## Currently, bools are represented like this:\r\n`0 = true`\r\n`1 = false`\r\n\r\n## I have tried out how several bools can be represented as an [u8](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/primitive.u8.html):\r\n\r\n### Double Bool\r\n`0 = false, false`\r\n`1 = false, true`\r\n`2 = true, false`\r\n`3 = true, true`\r\n\r\n### Other examples\r\n\r\nI once calculated how much you can save with this.\r\nThe maximum value of a u8 is 255.\r\n\r\n2^2 = 4 (double bool - 2 bools with 4 possibilities)\r\n3^3 = 27 (triple bool - 3 bools with 27 possibilities)\r\n4^4 = 256 (maxed bool - 4 bools with 256 possibilities)\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "jonas-schievink", "id": 1786438, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE3ODY0Mzg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1786438?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonas-schievink", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/69093/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes"